    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Peiping (
                        Clubb
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1244</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1244</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-11-09T02:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-11-09T02:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-09T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-09T02:00:00-05:00" n="1244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1244">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00B/11–949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-09T15:00:00+08:00">November 9, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 9—4:16 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1954. ReDeptel 778, November 8.<note n="54" xml:id="d1244fn54">Not printed; it
                        stated: “Dept will release text ur Nov 3 ltr to Chou En-lai at press
                        conference Nov 9.” (893.00B/11–849) See press release of November 10,
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, November 21, 1949, p.
                        759.</note> Agree re desirability releasing at this time text letter
                    November 3 to Chou En-lai.</p>
                <p>Letter still unacknowledged and no answer from Foreign Office to my letter of
                    October 31 requesting interview.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
